revision.text:
'''Ælfwald''' was a [[List of monarchs of Sussex|King of Sussex]], who reigned jointly with [[Ealdwulf of Sussex|Ealdwulf]] and [[Oslac of Sussex|Oslac]], and probably also with [[Oswald of Sussex|Oswald]] and [[Osmund of Sussex|Osmund]].
Ælfwald witnessed an undated charter of Ealdwulf, believed to be from about 765, with his name corruptly recorded as ''Ælhuuald rex''.<ref>Kelly 1.</ref>
Ælfwald also witnessed a charter of [[Offa of Mercia|Offa]], King of Mercia, dated 772, as ''Ælbuuald dux'',<ref>Flaherty 36.</ref> with his name placed after Oswald, Osmund, but before Oslac.
He is not known to have issued charters of his own.
