'''Boiorix''' was a king of the [[Cimbri]] tribe during the [[Cimbrian War]]. His most notable achievement was the victory against the [[Ancient Rome|Romans]] at the [[Battle of Arausio]] in 105 BC.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.livius.org/li-ln/livy/periochae/periochae066.html#67 |title=Periochae of Books 66-70 |author=Livy |authorlink=Livy |accessdate=5 October 2010}}</ref> He was later defeated and slain along with [[Lugius]] at the [[Battle of Vercellae]] in 101 BC. The other Cimbrian chiefs [[Claodicus]] and [[Caesorix]] were captured.<ref>{{cite book |last=Sampson |first=Gareth S. |authorlink= |title=The crisis of Rome: the Jugurthine and Northern Wars and the rise of Marius |url=https://books.google.no/books?id=zUQpAQAAMAAJ&q=%22The+kings+Lugius+and+Boiorix+fell+on+the+battlefield;+Claodicus+and+Caesorix+were+captured%22&dq=%22The+kings+Lugius+and+Boiorix+fell+on+the+battlefield;+Claodicus+and+Caesorix+were+captured%22&hl=no&sa=X&ei=1DG6UP-DBcvU4QSZloCICQ&ved=0CDMQ6AEwAA |accessdate=1 December 2012 |year=2010 |publisher=Pen & Sword Military |location= |isbn= |page=175 |pages=}}</ref>
