==Production==
[[File:ForeverPoster.png|thumb|right|135px|Promotional poster.]]

===Development===
On September 8, 2017, it was announced that Amazon had given the production a straight-to-series order consisting of one season. The series was created by [[Alan Yang]] and [[Matt Hubbard]] who are set to executive produce the series alongside [[Fred Armisen]], [[Maya Rudolph]], Dave Becky, and [[Tim Sarkes]]. Production companies expected to be involved with the series included [[Universal Television]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title=Amazon Orders Fred Armisen-Maya Rudolph Comedy & Wong Kar-wai Drama Series; Greg Daniels, Bays-Thomas Pilots|url=http://deadline.com/2017/09/amazon-fred-armisen-maya-rudolph-comedy-wong-kar-wai-drama-series-greg-daniels-carter-bays-craig-thomas-comedy-pilots-1202164882/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=February 20, 2018|date=September 9, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Holloway|first1=Daniel|last2=Littleton|first2=Cynthia|title=Amazon Orders Fred Armisen-Maya Rudolph Comedy, Wong Kar-wai Drama, 3 Other Projects (EXCLUSIVE)|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/amazon-armisen-rudolph-wong-1202552683/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=February 20, 2018|date=September 9, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Ivie|first1=Devon|title=Why Fred Armisen and Maya Rudolph’s New Show Might Become the Funniest on TV|url=http://www.vulture.com/2017/09/fred-armisen-and-maya-rudolph-are-starring-in-amazon-comedy.html|website=Vulture|accessdate=February 20, 2018|language=en|date=September 9, 2017}}</ref> On December 21, 2017, it was reported that the series was expected to debut in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Evans|first1=Greg|title=Amazon Prime Unveils 2018 Original Program Slate|url=http://deadline.com/2017/12/amazon-prime-2018-original-program-slate-premiere-dates-1202231124/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=February 20, 2018|date=December 21, 2017}}</ref> On August 2, 2018, it was announced that the series would premiere on September 14, 2018.<ref name="Premiere"/>

===Casting===
Alongside the initial series announcement, it was reported that Armisen and Rudolph were cast in the series' lead roles.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lawrence|first1=Derek|title=Amazon Gives Series Order to Maya Rudolph, Fred Armisen Comedy|url=http://ew.com/tv/2017/09/08/amazon-series-order-maya-rudolph-fred-armisen-comedy/|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=February 20, 2018|language=en|date=September 8, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Schwartz|first1=Ryan|title=Fred Armisen/Maya Rudolph Comedy Gets Series Order at Amazon|url=http://tvline.com/2017/09/09/fred-armisen-maya-rudolph-amazon-comedy-series-order/|website=[[TVLine]]|accessdate=February 20, 2018|date=September 9, 2017}}</ref> On December 1, 2017, it was announced that [[Catherine Keener]] had joined the series in a recurring role.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title=Catherine Keener Joins Fred Armisen-Maya Rudolph Amazon Comedy Series As Recurring|url=http://deadline.com/2017/12/catherine-keener-recur-fred-armisen-maya-rudolph-amazon-comedy-1202218192/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=February 20, 2018|date=December 1, 2017}}</ref>

==Release==
On August 2, 2018, the first trailer and poster for the series were released.<ref name="Premiere"/>

==Reception==
The series has been met with a positive response from critics upon its premiere. On the [[review aggregation]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the first season holds a 94% approval rating, with an average rating of 7.61 out of 10 based on 35 reviews. The website's critical consensus reads, "''Forever'' is a gently harrowing and mirthful dive into the ennui of matrimony, elevated by Maya Rudolph's dazzling turn of not-so-quiet desperation."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/forever_2018/s01/|title=Forever: Season 1 |website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango Media|Fandango]]|accessdate=October 19, 2018}}</ref> [[Metacritic]], which uses a weighted average, assigned the season a score of 77 out of 100 based on 20 critics, indicating "generally favorable reviews."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/forever-2018|title=Forever: Season 1 |website=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=September 21, 2018}}</ref>

