[[Image:Larryy Yaeger.jpg|right|thumb|Larry Yaeger in 2005, with Polyworld running in the background]] '''Larry Steven Yaeger''' (1950) is a former Apple Distinguished Scientist and Full Professor of Informatics at [[Indiana University Bloomington]], currently employed at [[Google]]. Outside of academia he is best known for designing the [[handwriting recognition]] software used in the [[Apple Newton]] and [[Inkwell]]. Yaeger's academic research focused on the evolution of true [[artificial intelligence]] through [[natural selection]]. He is the lead developer of [[Polyworld]].
